"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/766109","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-16","<p>The Government has been clear from the start that the devolved administrations should be fully engaged in our exit from the EU. The Government’s recent paper: The exchange and protection of personal data - a future partnership paper, and others provide a basis for further discussion, including with the devolved administrations, on the future partnership the UK wants to build with the EU. We have shared papers in advance with the devolved administrations and provided technical briefings ahead of publication.</p><p> </p><p>Ministers and officials regularly meet with their counterparts at the Scottish Government to discuss a range of matters, including on the future partnership between the UK and the EU.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","106398","2017-10-16T16:43:57.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/766109/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/766109/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/766109/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-06","Personal Records: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to the policy paper, The exchange and protection of personal data: a future partnership paper, published on 24 August 2017, what discussions the Government has had with the Scottish Government on the proposed UK-EU model for exchanging and protecting personal data.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","106397"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/766110","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-16","<p>I refer the Hon member to the responses I gave in the Chamber during the Leaving the EU: Data Protection debate on Thursday 12 October.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","106384 ; 106386 ; 106388 ; 106389 ; 106391 ; 106392 ; 106393 ; 106394 ; 106395","2017-10-16T16:35:09.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/766110/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/766110/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/766110/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-06","Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to the policy paper, The exchange and protection of personal data: a future partnership paper, published on 24 August 2017, what assessment her Department has made of the effect on UK GDP of UK-EU data flows being disrupted by the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","106385"
