"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760667","Department for International Trade","false","2017-10-12","<p>Licence applicants are required to provide full details of the proposed end-use of the items to be exported. These are then assessed as part of the licence application process, which is considered against the Consolidated EU and National Arms Export Criteria. Post export, the Department receives information from a variety of sources, either directly or via other Government Departments, including from Non-Government Organisations and through diplomatic reporting.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-10-12T11:40:30.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760667/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760667/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/760667/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-09-14","Arms Trade: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what information his Department receives on the end use of UK arms exports.","false","Biography information for Ann Clwyd","Cynon Valley","Ann Clwyd","105242"
